    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Hey guys, I know many of you have thought about ways to reinvent or change how you generate income the past years. I also had to rethink my income setup and I’d like to share with you my story of how I have created actual working income streams using my data science knowledge.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">BUT before I do, I want you to know that I didn’t do this overnight. In fact, most of these income streams took at least a year to build before I got anything substantial out of them. Hence, they are no get-rich-quick scheme tips, but rather real life lessons that can be reproduced.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-10">
            <br>
                <hr class="hr5">
            <br>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content7 cid-ttbhFZC4Ql" id="content7-8" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
        <div class="container"><div class="row justify-content-center"><div class="col-12 col-md-9"><blockquote><p class="ff4"><strong>Be sure to </strong><a href="https://medium.com/@janschmitz_80340/membership" target="_self">SUBSCRIBE here</a><strong> to never miss another article on data science, investing, life lessons, and more!</strong></p></blockquote></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-10">
            <br>
                <hr class="hr5">
            <br>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><h4 class="mbr-section-subtitle mbr-fonts-style mb-4 display-5"><strong>1. Career as a Data Scientist</strong></h4></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">A job in the data science field seems to be an obvious choice to generate an income stream using data science. However, this one is the most important one, since it provides you with two things that you can leverage later down the road.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Firstly, it provides you the opportunity to consistently <strong>sharpen your data science skills</strong> during the day and secondly, it <strong>supplies you with a large portion of capital</strong> that you will later use to generate other income streams.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">I personally had an unconventional start as a data scientist. I had my initial contact with the data science field during the early phases of my first own startup. We were building an ERP tool for construction industries so that players like general contractors had the ability to have a clean offer and invoice generation flow. With all the collected pricing data that came from the offers and invoices I built a product extension that showed during the offer creation the likelihood that an offer would convert. Calculating the likelihood was mainly based on the competitiveness of the pricing compared to other competitors in the region.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">This product extension turned out to be the biggest selling point of our own ERP system. Since it solved the problem of extreme intransparency within in the industry.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">After my own startup, I decided to work 100% as a data scientist and started at Mercedes-Benz, where we built an extensive data and model infrastructure to facilitate automatic car accident detection and easing mechanisms. Our objective was to make driving significantly safer and provide an “everything is taken care off” experience in case something happens.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">After leaving Mercedes and switching into a more generalistic role I am right now responsible for the Customer Data Platform at one of Germany's biggest corporates. Making sure that millions of customers are understood and reached during the right time, with the right messaging, and content.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content7 cid-ttbhFZC4Ql" id="content7-8" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
        <div class="container"><div class="row justify-content-center"><div class="col-12 col-md-9"><blockquote><p class="ff4">The common theme during all my career stages has been to make sure that we <strong>always solve serious problems for our customers.</strong></p></blockquote></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Having a data science perspective offers the unique ability to analytically minimize bias, and optimized the understanding of your customer. Therefore, your main goal should be to learn concepts and topics that will help you to make sense of your customer and hence make you advance in your own career.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><h4 class="mbr-section-subtitle mbr-fonts-style mb-4 display-5">2. Investing as a Data Scientist</h4></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">The second income stream I want to talk about is <strong>investing</strong>. After having worked for a couple of years as a data scientist I was able to save up a reasonable amount and I felt the urge to switch from saving to investing. Instead of letting my savings be eaten up by inflation over the years, I decided to make my money work for me.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">I quickly came to the conclusion that real estate is not an investment for me since I don’t want to add the stress of dealing with tenants to my daily life. Thus, I deep dived into stocks, ETFs, funds, and crypto currencies. Instead of simply relying on the advice of others, I rolled up my data science sleeves and tackled the problem with an analytical mindset.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content7 cid-ttbhFZC4Ql" id="content7-8" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
        <div class="container"><div class="row justify-content-center"><div class="col-12 col-md-9"><blockquote><p class="ff4">My objective was to find out what assets to buy, maximizing my returns but keeping my risk low</p></blockquote></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">At the beginning, like everyone I started with a very simple portfolio optimization which relied on a <a href="http://www.columbia.edu/~mh2078/FoundationsFE/MeanVariance-CAPM.pdf" target="_self">Mean-Variance Optimization</a> that weighted expected returns of an asset against its risk and subsequently considered the covariance of multiple assets to decide what stocks, ETFs, funds or cryptos shall go into my portfolio.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Over time my models for return and especially risk predictions became more and more refined. However, the hardest nut which I had to crack was figuring out how to build a reliable data pipeline that accesses high-quality data to describe the markets from different angles e.g. news, prices, and consumer good prices to calculate inflation. Overtime, my data pipelines improved a lot as well which caused the major difference in the prediction quality. In the past I shared a few articles with you guys to document my journey.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><div class="sketchy"><a href="https://towardsdatascience.com/stock-predictions-with-state-of-the-art-transformer-and-time-embeddings-3a4485237de6"><h2 style="color:blueviolet; font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size:25px;">Stock predictions with state-of-the-art Transformer and Time Embeddings</h2><h3 style="color:rgb(45, 34, 54); font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size:20px;">Feeding a trading bot with state-of-the-art stock predictions</h3><p>towardsdatascience.com</p></a></div></div></div></div></section><br><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Due to the rigorous improvements of my models and data pipelines have been able to grow the returns of my investments into my second largest income stream. Creating an infrastructure that analyses information from thousands of assets from different asset classes (stocks, ETFs, funds and cryptos) is not an easy task, but once in place provides tremendous value.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">I received a lot of requests from friends to share or make my models or pipelines available, which I gladly did. However, this always came in conjunction with massive time investments for onboarding, since the project that I shared has grown for multiple years in size and complexity.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Thus, I started to developed an easy to use interface called <a href="https://www.pinklion.xyz/" target="_self">PinkLion</a> (naming still in discussion 😄) which lives on top of my code base and makes use of my own infrastructure. With the interface you can access with <strong>one-click</strong> the part of my code base that is responsible for the <strong>automatic asset analysis, selection</strong> and <strong>portfolio allocation.</strong></p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Right now it is still in a rough state, but I’d love to receive feedback on whether an <strong>automated assets selection</strong> and <strong>portfolio allocation </strong>is of use for anyone else.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;"><strong>Feel free to give it a try.</strong> On a side note, right now I have limited the number of signups, since the calculation in the background are very resource intensive and could easily bring down the servers.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content7 cid-ttbhFZC4Ql" id="content7-8" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
        <div class="container"><div class="row justify-content-center"><div class="col-12 col-md-9"><blockquote><p class="ff4"><strong>No more guesswork, use science when investing </strong><a href="https://www.pinklion.xyz/" target="_self">https://www.pinklion.xyz/</a></p></blockquote></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><div class="sketchy"><a href="https://www.pinklion.xyz/"><h2 style="color:blueviolet; font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size:25px;">PinkLion</h2><h3 style="color:rgb(45, 34, 54); font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size:20px;">No more guesswork, use data science when investing. Stock, funds, and crypto currencies in one place. Improve your portfolio with machine learning to increase returns and lower risk.</h3><p>www.pinklion.xyz</p></a></div></div></div></div></section><br><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><h4 class="mbr-section-subtitle mbr-fonts-style mb-4 display-5">3. Consulting as a Data Scientist</h4></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">The third stream of income that I wanted to talk about is my consulting practices. Here you might think that a list of — <em>“I have developed for a client a model X to perform a prediction for task Y” </em>— will await you. But this sort of work is usually <strong>not requested</strong> for consulting on data-related topics. Some of the consulting jobs I worked on include the following:</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><ul><li class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">I consulted a company on how to structure a <strong>MLOps pipeline</strong>. This included the operationalization of the pipeline as well as an educational part to provide the company with an understanding of how important version control is for data prep functions, datasets and not just the models themself.</li><li class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">I worked with a company to develop a framework to have a <strong>standardized process in place to track biases</strong> in datasets and data artifacts. Having a reproducible and regioures biases detection helps to avoid out of sample issues when deploying models to production. Which is usually a big hurdle for data science projects to delivery business value.</li><li class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">I advised a startup during their growth phase on what relevant <strong>KPIs and metrics</strong> are to focus on when <strong>setting up a data team</strong> and how the metrics in focus, have to shift when the data team is growing in size.</li></ul></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">As a conclusion, data-related consulting gigs usually do not focus on the development of a particular model to produce some sort of prediction, but rather focus on more high-level problems that are related to structuring an organization. <mark>Hence, it is very important to understand that your data science skill set shall not just be used to develop a stand alone model ,but rather on how data driven processes can be established and lived.</mark></p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
